{
  "texts": [
    "Intuitively, the Table 5: Evaluation on the shifted distribution settings.",
    "fine-tuned models themselves cannot be evaluated in the cross-dataset setting due to the different entity type sets between the source and target datasets.",
    "Thus, we denote them as not applicable (N/A) in Table 4.",
    "On the contrary, the fine-tuned models equipped with VERIFINER perform much better than the prompting-based LLM (GPT-NER), and even achieve comparable performance to baselines trained on the target dataset.",
    "This suggests that VERIFINER can heighten the performance of finetuned NER models on unseen datasets, where the training dataset is not accessible."
  ]
}